    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 100ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [200ml] </span><strong>milk</strong> and 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml]</span> <strong>water </strong>to<strong> </strong>a pot over a medium heat</p><p>While the milk warms, mix<strong> half</strong> <span class=\"text-danger\">[all] </span>of the <strong>cornflour </strong>(cooking for 2? Save the rest for another recipe!) with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]<strong> </span>water</strong> to form a smooth paste in a bowl</p><p>Once the milk has warmed, add the <strong>cornflour paste </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened</p><p>Add the <strong>soft cheese</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and<strong> half</strong> of the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> – this is your <strong>béchamel sauce</strong></p>",
